<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND COOLER - OIL COOLER -
        REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350813">8.13</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            .
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>USE NEW O-RING WHEN ASSEMBLING THE OIL COOLER ASSEMBLY.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>USE ONLY CLEAN ENGINE OIL FOR O-RING LUBRICATION.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>REPLACE O-RINGS WHICH MAY BE DAMAGED (NICKS OR CUTS, ETC.) DURING INSTALLATION.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using clean engine oil, lubricate the oil cooler bundle headers at the O-Ring mating
                surfaces.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the large O-Rings on the oil cooler bundle first, then install the small O-Rings on
                the cooler bundle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully press assembly together assuring that the locating clip of the oil cooler rear
                header aligns in the slot of the cooler bundle and header is not cocked.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The oil filter by-pass and oil pressure regulator, which are housed in the oil filter-cooler
                        header, are not serviced separately.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350813" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11129" filename="../figcg1/CG11129.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8.13</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Front header shown, the rear header is assembled similarly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
